Suspected gang boss and alleged fraudster Shaun Ah Shene appeared briefly in the Port Elizabeth Specialised Commercial Crimes Court yesterday for allegedly defrauding the SA Revenue Service of R2.1-million. Ah Shene was arrested two years ago during a raid by the Hawks on his Adcockvale family home. Ah Shene and his business, Coral Blue Trading CC, face eight counts of fraud over a period of six years. His assets – including 21 investment accounts and 13 properties, and cash – were placed in the hands of a curator shortly after his arrest. The case was postponed to April 13. Suspected gang boss Shaun Ah Shene appeared briefly in the Port Elizabeth Commercial Crimes Court yesterday for allegedly defrauding the South African Revenue Service (SARS) to the tune of about R2.1-million. His case was postponed to February 27 after his attorney, Carolyn Ah Shene-Verdoom, said she would make representations to… December 6, 2017 The assets of suspected gang boss Shaun Ah Shene were finally restrained in the Port Elizabeth High Court on Tuesday. Ah Shene and his company Coral Blue Trading CC are accused of defrauding the taxman out of more than R2.1-million. The assets now placed in the hands of the curator… May 10, 2016 Suspected gang leader Shaun Ah Shene was arrested at his Parsons Hill home this morning (29/10/15). Ah Shene is being booked at Mount Road police station and is expected to appear in the Port Elizabeth Magistrate's Court later today. He was arrested for  fraud, tax evasion and under the Prevention of… October 29, 2015